(Photo: W&M Athletics) CONNECT TWEET   Tribe is up several spots in the FCS polls. 13News Now 
WILLIAMSBURG, VA -After earning its second consecutive victory in convincing fashion against a nationally ranked team, the William & Mary football team made significant leaps in both major Football Championship Subdivision (FCS) polls this week. W&M (4-2, 3-1) jumped up eight spots to No. 16 in the Coaches Poll, while it moved up seven places to No. 17 in the STATS Poll. Both polls are available at 
http://www.ncaa.com/rankings/football/fc . 
Off to a 3-1 start in conference play, W&M's has performed well on both sides of the ball this season. In addition to leading the CAA and ranking 10th nationally in scoring defense (16.7), the Tribe is averaging 29.8 points per game and 424.3 total yards per contest.  //on.wvec.com/1LHzLak TOP VIDEOS
